<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="492" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,835,2014]" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">
At present, three genera and seven species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stach" authorityYear="1949" box="[656,866,835,861]" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Brachystomellidae</taxonomicName>
are known from 
<collectingCountry box="[1056,1198,835,861]" name="South Africa" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">South Africa</collectingCountry>
including 
<taxonomicName authority="Janion-Scheepers &amp; Deharveng, 2022" authorityName="Janion-Scheepers &amp; Deharveng" authorityYear="2022" box="[1316,1436,835,861]" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" genus="Setanodosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jacquesi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1316,1436,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">S. jacquesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,241,871,897]" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,241,871,897]" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
The map (
<figureCitation box="[363,431,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1355,1379]" captionTargetBox="[151,1398,181,1332]" captionTargetId="figure-18@10.[151,1436,181,1332]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 9. Distribution map of Setanodosa jacquesi sp. nov. and Brachystomellidae recorded to date from South Africa based on the checklist of South African Collembola (Janion-Scheepers et al. 2015) and barcoded material (Table 1)." pageId="9" pageNumber="492">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) indicates the geographical locations of published records (
<bibRefCitation author="Janion-Scheepers, C. &amp; Deharveng, L. &amp; Bedos, A. &amp; Chown, S. L." box="[1101,1429,871,898]" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" pagination="55 - 88" refId="ref6263" refString="Janion-Scheepers, C., Deharveng, L., Bedos, A. &amp; Chown, S. L. (2015) Updated list of Collembola species currently recorded from South Africa. ZooKeys, 503, 55 - 88. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 503.8966" type="journal article" year="2015">
Janion-Scheepers 
<emphasis box="[1307,1357,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
) and barcoded specimen records of this study. It highlights large geographical gaps, which are not real, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Agren" authorityYear="1903" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" genus="Brachystomella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">Brachystomella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widespread and common in most regions of 
<collectingCountry box="[771,917,943,969]" name="South Africa" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">South Africa</collectingCountry>
. All species are known from the southern part of the country as most collection efforts have been concentrated in this area (
<bibRefCitation author="Janion-Scheepers, C. &amp; Deharveng, L. &amp; Bedos, A. &amp; Chown, S. L." box="[999,1326,979,1006]" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" pagination="55 - 88" refId="ref6263" refString="Janion-Scheepers, C., Deharveng, L., Bedos, A. &amp; Chown, S. L. (2015) Updated list of Collembola species currently recorded from South Africa. ZooKeys, 503, 55 - 88. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 503.8966" type="journal article" year="2015">
Janion-Scheepers 
<emphasis box="[1203,1252,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
). Interestingly, a single record of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stach" authorityYear="1949" box="[422,632,1015,1041]" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Brachystomellidae</taxonomicName>
has been published for the whole Ethiopian region outside 
<collectingCountry box="[1294,1437,1015,1041]" name="South Africa" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">South Africa</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Thibaud, J. M." box="[159,321,1051,1077]" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" pagination="233 - 248" refId="ref6885" refString="Thibaud, J. M. (2013) Essai sur l'etat des connaissances de la diversite des Collemboles de l'Empire Africano-Malgache. Russian Entomological Journal, 22 (4), 233 - 248. https: // doi. org / 10.15298 / rusentj. 23.4.01" type="journal article" year="2013">Thibaud 2013</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Denis, 1931" authorityName="Denis" authorityYear="1931" box="[341,763,1051,1077]" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" genus="Brachystomella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="contorta">
<emphasis box="[341,620,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">Brachystomella contorta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Denis, J. R." box="[627,763,1051,1077]" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" pagination="69 - 170" refId="ref5893" refString="Denis, J. R. (1931) Contributo a la conoscenza del &quot; Microgenton &quot; di Costa Rica. II-Collemboles de Costa Rica avec une contribution au species de l'ordre. Bolletino del Laboratorio di Zoologia Generale e Agraria, 15, 69 - 170." type="journal article" year="1931">Denis, 1931</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[833,968,1051,1078]" name="Ivory Coast" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">Ivory Coast</collectingCountry>
, a species considered as pantropical (
<bibRefCitation author="Zon, S. D. &amp; Thibaud, J. M. &amp; Tano, Y." pageId="9" pageNumber="492" pagination="91 - 96" refId="ref7128" refString="Zon, S. D., Thibaud, J. M. &amp; Tano, Y. (2013) Etats des connaissances sur les Collemboles de Cote d'Ivoire (Afrique de l'ouest) (Collembola). Russian Entomological Journal, 22 (2), 91 - 96." type="journal article" year="2013">
Zon 
<emphasis box="[151,207,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
). This species was not present in the material examined so far from 
<collectingCountry box="[1034,1179,1087,1113]" name="South Africa" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">South Africa</collectingCountry>
. Despite the paucity of distributional data, the rarity of the family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stach" authorityYear="1949" box="[633,843,1123,1149]" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Brachystomellidae</taxonomicName>
north of southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1052,1195,1123,1149]" name="South Africa" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">South Africa</collectingCountry>
may reflect the wellknown global pattern of a southern hemisphere distribution of the family, which is extensively documented in the literature (
<bibRefCitation author="Najt, J. &amp; Weiner, W. M." box="[267,498,1195,1221]" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" pagination="61 - 69" refId="ref6547" refString="Najt, J. &amp; Weiner, W. M. (1996) Geographical distribution of Brachystomellinae (Collembola, Neanurinae). Pan-Pacific Entomologist, 72, 61 - 69." type="journal article" year="1996">Najt &amp; Weiner 1996</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Weiner, W. M. &amp; Najt, J." box="[509,739,1195,1221]" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" pagination="387 - 413" refId="ref6968" refString="Weiner, W. M. &amp; Najt, J. (2001) Species of Brachystomella (Collembola. Brachystomellidae) from the Neotropical region. European Journal of Entomology, 98 (3), 387 - 413. https: // doi. org / 10.14411 / eje. 2001.059" type="journal article" year="2001">Weiner &amp; Najt 2001</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Greenslade, P." box="[750,944,1195,1221]" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" pagination="117 - 128" refId="ref6112" refString="Greenslade, P. (2018) Conspectus of Australian Brachystomellidae (Collembola) with description of new species of Rapoportella and redescription of Cassagnella anomala. European Journal of Entomology, 115, 117 - 128. https: // doi. org / 10.14411 / eje. 2018.010" type="journal article" year="2018">Greenslade 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,835,2014]" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">
One genus (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Weiner &amp; Najt" authorityYear="1991" box="[334,579,1231,1257]" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" genus="Probrachystomellides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[334,579,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">Probrachystomellides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and four species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stach" authorityYear="1949" box="[814,1024,1231,1257]" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Brachystomellidae</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Weiner &amp; Najt" authorityYear="1991" box="[1040,1153,1231,1257]" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" genus="Probrachystomellides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nicolaii">
<emphasis box="[1040,1153,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">P. nicolaii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yosii" authorityYear="1959" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" genus="Brachystomella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="parvula" subSpecies="africana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">Brachystomella parvula africana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Weiner &amp; Najt" authorityYear="1991" box="[261,372,1268,1293]" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" genus="Brachystomella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coatesi">
<emphasis box="[261,372,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">B. coatesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Weiner &amp; Najt" authorityYear="1991" box="[428,579,1268,1293]" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" genus="Brachystomella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="georgensis">
<emphasis box="[428,579,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">B. georgensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) are endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[771,917,1267,1293]" name="South Africa" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">South Africa</collectingCountry>
. One additional species of 
<emphasis box="[1222,1404,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Agren" authorityYear="1903" box="[1222,1401,1267,1293]" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" genus="Brachystomella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Brachystomella</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Schaffer, 1896)" baseAuthorityName="Schaffer" baseAuthorityYear="1896" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" genus="Brachystomella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parvula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">B. parvula</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Schaffer, C." box="[254,421,1303,1330]" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" pagination="149 - 216" refId="ref6760" refString="Schaffer, C. (1896) Die Collembola der Umgebung von Hamburg. Mitteilungen aus dem Naturhistorischen Museum in Hamburg, 13, 149 - 216." type="journal article" year="1896">Schäffer, 1896</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, has a wider distribution and is possibly introduced. This species, considered cosmopolitan in distribution (
<bibRefCitation author="Fjellberg, A." box="[367,537,1339,1365]" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" pagination="1 - 183" refId="ref6004" refString="Fjellberg, A. (1998) The Collembola of Fennoscandia and Denmark. Part I. Poduromorpha. Fauna Entomologica Scandinavica, 35, 1 - 183." type="journal article" year="1998">Fjellberg 1998</bibRefCitation>
), is the most frequently cited from 
<collectingCountry box="[937,1083,1339,1365]" name="South Africa" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">South Africa</collectingCountry>
, but these ancient records need confirmation, as we have not found it so far in our samples (since 2008). According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Weiner, W. M. &amp; Najt, J." box="[1125,1373,1375,1401]" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" pagination="369 - 387" refId="ref6933" refString="Weiner, W. M. &amp; Najt, J. (1991) Collembola Poduromorpha of South Africa. Bonner zoologische Beitrage, 42 (3 - 4), 369 - 387." type="journal article" year="1991">Weiner &amp; Najt (1991)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Najt &amp; Massoud, 1974" authorityName="Najt &amp; Massoud" authorityYear="1974" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" genus="Brachystomella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">Brachystomella platensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Najt, J. &amp; Massoud, Z." box="[399,658,1411,1437]" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" pagination="367 - 372" refId="ref6503" refString="Najt, J. &amp; Massoud, Z. (1974) Contribution l'etude des Brachystomellinae (Insectes, Collemboles. I. - Nouvelles especes recoltees en Argentine. Revue d'Ecologie et de Biologie du Sol, 11, 367 - 372." type="journal article" year="1974">Najt &amp; Massoud, 1974</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, described from South America (
<bibRefCitation author="Najt, J. &amp; Massoud, Z." box="[1027,1279,1411,1437]" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" pagination="367 - 372" refId="ref6503" refString="Najt, J. &amp; Massoud, Z. (1974) Contribution l'etude des Brachystomellinae (Insectes, Collemboles. I. - Nouvelles especes recoltees en Argentine. Revue d'Ecologie et de Biologie du Sol, 11, 367 - 372." type="journal article" year="1974">Najt &amp; Massoud 1974</bibRefCitation>
) where it was probably introduced, but mostly present in 
<collectingCountry box="[645,748,1447,1473]" name="Australia" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">Australia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Greenslade, P. &amp; Najt, J." box="[764,1048,1447,1473]" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" pagination="435 - 453" refId="ref6162" refString="Greenslade, P. &amp; Najt, J. (1987) Collemboles Brachystomellinae de l'Australie. I. Les genres Brachystomella et Rapoportella. Annales de la Societ Entomologique de. France, 4, 435 - 453." type="journal article" year="1987">Greenslade &amp; Najt 1987</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Najt, J. &amp; Weiner, W. M." box="[1061,1297,1447,1473]" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" pagination="61 - 69" refId="ref6547" refString="Najt, J. &amp; Weiner, W. M. (1996) Geographical distribution of Brachystomellinae (Collembola, Neanurinae). Pan-Pacific Entomologist, 72, 61 - 69." type="journal article" year="1996">Najt &amp; Weiner 1996</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Greenslade, P." pageId="9" pageNumber="492" pagination="117 - 128" refId="ref6112" refString="Greenslade, P. (2018) Conspectus of Australian Brachystomellidae (Collembola) with description of new species of Rapoportella and redescription of Cassagnella anomala. European Journal of Entomology, 115, 117 - 128. https: // doi. org / 10.14411 / eje. 2018.010" type="journal article" year="2018">Greenslade 2018</bibRefCitation>
), is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Weiner &amp; Najt" authorityYear="1991" box="[459,612,1484,1509]" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" genus="Brachystomella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="georgensis">
<emphasis box="[459,612,1484,1509]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">B. georgensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from which it differs by a few characters. We provisionally assigned the specimens of most South African populations that we have barcoded to this species, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Najt &amp; Massoud" authorityYear="1974" box="[1154,1291,1519,1545]" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" genus="Brachystomella" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platensis">
cf. 
<emphasis box="[1191,1291,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">platensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation box="[1307,1393,1519,1545]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="7.[151,239,468,494]" captionText="TABLE 1. Details of barcoded specimens (see Figs 8 and 9)." pageId="9" pageNumber="492">Table 1</tableCitation>
). A most interesting side-result of our study is that COI sequences of specimens of this species from 
<collectingCountry box="[1261,1364,1555,1581]" name="Australia" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">Australia</collectingCountry>
(Melbourne) are identical to those of specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[706,852,1591,1617]" name="South Africa" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">South Africa</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Najt &amp; Massoud" authorityYear="1974" box="[864,1183,1591,1617]" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" genus="Brachystomella" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platensis">
<emphasis box="[864,1040,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">Brachystomella</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis box="[1083,1183,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">platensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is therefore present in both regions. Its identity is however uncertain, given in particular its similarity with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Weiner &amp; Najt" authorityYear="1991" box="[1128,1281,1628,1653]" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" genus="Brachystomella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="georgensis">
<emphasis box="[1128,1281,1628,1653]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">B. georgensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This will be checked in further morphological and molecular studies which are beyond the scope of this paper. The only species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salmon" authorityYear="1942" box="[233,362,1699,1725]" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" genus="Setanodosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[233,362,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">Setanodosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described from 
<collectingCountry box="[547,693,1699,1725]" name="South Africa" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">South Africa</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Womersley" baseAuthorityYear="1934" box="[705,825,1699,1725]" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" genus="Setanodosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capitata">
<emphasis box="[705,825,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">S. capitata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, has also been recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[1164,1267,1699,1725]" name="Australia" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">Australia</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Womersley, H." pageId="9" pageNumber="492" refId="ref7051" refString="Womersley, H. (1939) Primitive Insects of South Australia. S. A. Branch Brit. Sci. Guild, Adelaide, 322 pp." type="book" year="1939">Womersley (1939)</bibRefCitation>
, a record which seeks confirmation (
<bibRefCitation author="Greenslade, P." box="[640,835,1735,1761]" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" refId="ref6061" refString="Greenslade, P. (1994) Collembola. In: Houston, W. W. K. (Ed.), Zoological catalogue of Australia. Vol. 22. Protura, Collembola, Diplur a. CSIRO Australia, Melbourne, pp. 19 - 138." type="book" year="1994">Greenslade 1994</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,835,2014]" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Agren" authorityYear="1903" box="[325,501,1771,1797]" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" genus="Brachystomella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[325,501,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">Brachystomella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is by far the most common in soils of southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1051,1198,1771,1797]" name="South Africa" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">South Africa</collectingCountry>
, with several unpublished records of unidentified species that were not considered in this paper. Ecologically, it is present in soil, less frequently in more xeric habitats. The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salmon" authorityYear="1942" box="[678,807,1843,1869]" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" genus="Setanodosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[678,807,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">Setanodosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is much less frequently observed. Morphologically, it corresponds to the “hemiedaphon xerophil” biological form of 
<bibRefCitation author="Gisin, H." box="[865,1010,1879,1905]" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" pagination="131 - 224" refId="ref6033" refString="Gisin, H. (1943) Okologie und Lebensgemeinschaften der Collembolen im schweizerischen Exkursionsgebiet Basels. Revue Suisse de Zoologie, 50, 131 - 224." type="journal article" year="1943">Gisin (1943)</bibRefCitation>
, with its very developed and strongly clavate tenent hairs. The genus is found on rocks but is also present in litter. However, the number of records, most of unidentified species, is not enough to speculate on the ecology of 
<taxonomicName box="[924,1150,1951,1977]" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" genus="Setanodosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[924,1053,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">Setanodosa</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
The third genus, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Weiner &amp; Najt" authorityYear="1991" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" genus="Probrachystomellides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Probrachystomellides</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
is only known so far from the 
<typeStatus box="[668,716,1988,2014]" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">type</typeStatus>
locality (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Weiner &amp; Najt" authorityYear="1991" box="[824,1162,1987,2013]" class="Collembola" family="Brachystomellidae" genus="Probrachystomellides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poduromorpha" pageId="9" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nicolaii">
<emphasis box="[824,1162,1987,2013]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="492">Probrachystomellides nicolaii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
